{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-js","path":"/blog/accidental-reset","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"46d8b5cc-fa2d-5eef-a21c-e3def4eac263","html":"<p>From page 33 of the <a href=\"http://www.librarything.com/work/52052\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Apple II User's Guide</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<h3 id=\"accidental-reset\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#accidental-reset\" aria-label=\"accidental reset permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Accidental Reset</h3>\n<p>Sooner or later you will hit the <code class=\"language-text\">RESET</code> key when you did not intend to. It is inevitable, unless your Apple II requires you to type <code class=\"language-text\">CTRL-RESET</code> instead of just plain <code class=\"language-text\">RESET</code>. You can reduce the hazard by carefully prying off the plastic keytop, leaving just the keyswitch shaft available (Figure 2-9).</p>\n<p>You can take this one step further and make it physically harder to push down the <code class=\"language-text\">RESET</code> key. Get a small rubber washer about 3/8 inches inner diameter, 1/2 inch outer diameter, and 1/8 inch thick. Remove the <code class=\"language-text\">RESET</code> keytop as shown in Figure 2-9. Work the washer over the exposed square flange of the keyshaft as shown in Figure 2-10. Replace the keytop.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Sometimes, all you need is a small rubber washer.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 640px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/09b6eef5160476a1e8744ad4371d0917/6af66/apple-ii-reset-key.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 37.65625%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Accidental Reset section of the Apple II User&#39;s Guide\"\n        title=\"Accidental Reset section of the Apple II User&#39;s Guide\"\n        src=\"/static/09b6eef5160476a1e8744ad4371d0917/6af66/apple-ii-reset-key.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/09b6eef5160476a1e8744ad4371d0917/d23e3/apple-ii-reset-key.png 169w,\n/static/09b6eef5160476a1e8744ad4371d0917/2b41d/apple-ii-reset-key.png 338w,\n/static/09b6eef5160476a1e8744ad4371d0917/6af66/apple-ii-reset-key.png 640w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>","fields":{"date":"April 14, 2014","slug":"/blog/accidental-reset","title":"Accidental reset"}}},"pageContext":{}}}